# Art Bible — {{projectName}}

> Visual style guide. Source of truth for **art** decisions. Reviewed at Phase 6 Content Gate **Art**.

## 1. Style

> One sentence + 3-5 reference images. The reference images live in `Assets/Art/_References/` (NOT shipped to runtime).

- **Sentence**: _e.g., "Hand-painted 2.5D platformer with bold silhouettes and 4-color shading per material"_
- **References**:
  - `Assets/Art/_References/ref-01.png`
  - `Assets/Art/_References/ref-02.png`

## 2. Palette

> Hex codes + named roles. Use these in Shader Graph constants and ScriptableObjects — do NOT hard-code in C#.

| Role | Hex | Hex (alt) | Use |
|---|---|---|---|
| Primary | `#E63946` | | Player, key interactables |
| Secondary | `#457B9D` | | Background depth layer 1 |
| Background | `#1D3557` | | Background depth layer 2 (Y < 0) |
| UI accent | `#F1FAEE` | | HUD, menu |
| Negative space | `#000000` | | Vignette, fade |

## 3. Pivot / scale conventions

- **Pixels-Per-Unit (PPU)**: `100` (must match `unity-2.5d-conventions` rule #7)
- **Sprite pivot**: Bottom for ground-aligned actors; Center for projectiles/icons
- **Reference unit**: 1 game-unit = 1 meter in world; 1 meter = 100 px at PPU 100

## 4. Forbidden list

> Things the art pipeline must refuse, even if the user asks. Saves explanation cycles. The `asset-pipeline` agent checks this list BEFORE every generation request.

- Hyper-realistic textures (clashes with hand-painted style)
- Per-pixel normal maps (mobile perf)
- More than 4 colors per material (palette discipline)
- Outlines drawn in sprite (use shader-based outline if needed)
- _add your own:_

## 5. Asset categories + budget

| Category | Polycount budget | Texture budget | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| Hero (player) | 8000 tris | 1024 ASTC 6x6 + 1024 normal | LOD0 only — no LOD swap on hero |
| NPC | 4000 tris (LOD0) / 1500 (LOD1) | 512 ASTC 6x6 | |
| Environment prop | 1500 tris | 512 ASTC 8x8 | shared atlas per zone |
| VFX | sprite sheet 1024x1024 | ETC2 RGBA8 | no PostFX-dependent effects |
| UI | vector or sprite | 256-1024 ASTC 6x6 | mipmaps OFF |

## 6. Out of scope (v1.0)

- Per-frame animation > 24 fps (use motion blur shader cheat)
- Procedural texture generation in-engine
